        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our science goals require us to match or supercede the HST-STIS observations of ionized gas in M87, made at a spatial resolution of 0.05arcsec and spectral resolution of 25 km/s.    Unfortunately, the TDM mode (velocity resolution of 26km/s per channel) is (just) too low for our purposes. We therefore use spectral mode, with 16 channel binning (final resolution 6 km/s) to reduce data rates, for each spw.   Some of the spw's are offset to avoid the overlapping which occurs if each is centered on its spectral line of interest.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The science aims set the resolution to be equal or better than 0.05"(to match HST-STIS ionized gas kinematic and stellar dynamic measurements). At the relatively high spectral resolution (6km/s) we use, and given the velocities seen in earlier lower resolution molecular gas kinematics (Vlahkis+) and ionized gas kinematics (Walsh+) we do not expect any given velocity channel to detect gas extended at more than a few arcsec.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>For dense gas tracers we use the previous observations of Vlahkis+ (from conference talks and from  ALMA archive data) to guide our integration times. Given the strong detection of these lines, and the fact that we are observing at increaseed resolution, we request line sensitivities about 3 times deeper.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
